      "retweeted_tweet_id": null,
      "text": "ICE HSI and its partners repatriated 26 ancient artifacts to the Hellenic Republic of Greece during a ceremony at the Embassy of Greece in Washington, D.C. April 23.\n\nThis marble torso of Asclepius, ancient Greek god of medicine and healing from the 1st or 2nd century, which stands 40 inches tall, was among the repatriated artifacts. Law enforcement seized it following an HSI and CBP investigation.\n\n🔎See more repatriated objects and learn more in our newsroom: https://t.co/5vn8PyNdsU",
      "text_resolved": "ICE HSI and its partners repatriated 26 ancient artifacts to the Hellenic Republic of Greece during a ceremony at the Embassy of Greece in Washington, D.C. April 23.\n\nThis marble torso of Asclepius, ancient Greek god of medicine and healing from the 1st or 2nd century, which stands 40 inches tall, was among the repatriated artifacts. Law enforcement seized it following an HSI and CBP investigation.\n\n🔎See more repatriated objects and learn more in our newsroom: https://www.ice.gov/news/releases/dhs-and-us-department-state-announce-return-stolen-cultural-property-hellenic",
