      "retweeted_tweet_id": null,
      "text": "Minh Duy Tong Nguyen aka Tony Playboy, of Vietnam, was once a fugitive wanted for the murder of two people and the attempted murder of three others. He was featured on an episode of \"America’s Most Wanted\" in 1990 and subsequently captured in Canada and extradited to the U.S. to stand trial for murder. \n\nHe was sentenced to 45-years in the state prison.\n\nICE @EROHouston took custody of him April 16, upon his release from prison.\n\nHis deportation order is over 25 years old.\n\nHe’s about to go home.",
      "text_resolved": "Minh Duy Tong Nguyen aka Tony Playboy, of Vietnam, was once a fugitive wanted for the murder of two people and the attempted murder of three others. He was featured on an episode of \"America’s Most Wanted\" in 1990 and subsequently captured in Canada and extradited to the U.S. to stand trial for murder. \n\nHe was sentenced to 45-years in the state prison.\n\nICE @EROHouston took custody of him April 16, upon his release from prison.\n\nHis deportation order is over 25 years old.\n\nHe’s about to go home.",
